{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addMainOption"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"entries"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GOptionEntry"},{"kind":"text","text":">!)"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is comparable to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_option_context_add_main_entries()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After the commandline arguments are parsed, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication::handle-local-options"},{"type":"text","text":" signal will be emitted.  At this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"point, the application can inspect the values pointed to by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the given "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionEntrys"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionContext"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" supports giving a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"type":"text","text":" for a non-callback "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionEntry"},{"type":"text","text":".  This results in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"argument in question being packed into a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVariantDict"},{"type":"text","text":" which is also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication::handle-local-options"},{"type":"text","text":", where it can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"inspected and modified.  If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_APPLICATION_HANDLES_COMMAND_LINE"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"set, then the resulting dictionary is sent to the primary instance,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_application_command_line_get_options_dict()"},{"type":"text","text":" will return it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"As it has been passed outside the process at this point, the types of all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values in the options dict must be checked before being used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This “packing” is done according to the type of the argument –"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"booleans for normal flags, strings for strings, bytestrings for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"filenames, etc.  The packing only occurs if the flag is given (ie: we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"do not pack a “false” "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVariant"},{"type":"text","text":" in the case that a flag is missing)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In general, it is recommended that all commandline arguments are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parsed locally.  The options dictionary should then be used to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"transmit the result of the parsing to the primary instance, where"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_dict_lookup()"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used.  For local options, it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"possible to either use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"type":"text","text":" in the usual way, or to consult (and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"potentially remove) the option from the options dictionary."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is new in GLib 2.40.  Before then, the only real choice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"was to send all of the commandline arguments (options and all) to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"primary instance for handling.  "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" ignored them completely"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the local side.  Calling this function “opts in” to the new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behaviour, and in particular, means that unrecognised options will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"treated as errors.  Unrecognised options have never been ignored when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_APPLICATION_HANDLES_COMMAND_LINE"},{"type":"text","text":" is unset."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication::handle-local-options"},{"type":"text","text":" needs to see the list of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"filenames, then the use of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_REMAINING"},{"type":"text","text":" is recommended.  If"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_REMAINING"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used as a key into"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the options dictionary.  If you do use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_REMAINING"},{"type":"text","text":" then you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"need to handle these arguments for yourself because once they are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consumed, they will no longer be visible to the default handling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(which treats them as filenames to be opened)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is important to use the proper GVariant format when retrieving"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the options with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_dict_lookup()"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_ARG_NONE"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_ARG_STRING"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"&s"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_ARG_INT"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"i"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_ARG_INT64"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_ARG_DOUBLE"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_ARG_FILENAME"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"^&ay"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_ARG_STRING_ARRAY"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"^a&s"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_OPTION_ARG_FILENAME_ARRAY"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"^a&ay"}]}]}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol\/addmainoption(entries:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol\/addMainOption(entries:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds main option entries to be handled by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"application"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"addMainOption(entries:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addMainOption"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"entries"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GOptionEntry"},{"kind":"text","text":">!)"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO19ApplicationProtocolPAAE13addMainOption7entriesySPySo13_GOptionEntryVGSg_tF","extendedModule":"GIO","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol"]]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"role":"collection","title":"GIO","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationProtocol/addMainOption(entries:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"addMainOption(entries:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addMainOption"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"entries"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GOptionEntry"},{"kind":"text","text":">!)"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds main option entries to be handled by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"application"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol\/addMainOption(entries:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol\/addmainoption(entries:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"ApplicationProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ApplicationProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" is the foundation of an application.  It wraps some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"low-level platform-specific services and is intended to act as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"foundation for higher-level application classes such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MxApplication"},{"type":"text","text":".  In general, you should not use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this class outside of a higher level framework."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ApplicationProtocol"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol"}}}